726173f-a.title: Queens: Borden Avenue - 11th Street
726173f-a.text:
Borden Avenue, north side, west from 11th Street, toward
the vehicular viaduct on Vernon Boulevard. All the structures
seen in this view, some of them (right) fronting on the south
side of 51st Avenue, were later torn down to make way for the
construction of the Queens-Midtown Tunnel plaza. The tall
building is the Clay Building, on Jaokson Avenue.
November 17, 1938
